==English==

===Etymology===
From [[bale]] + [[-er]].

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# A [[machine]] for creating [[bale]]s, e.g., of [[hay]] or [[cotton]].
#:''Farmer Jones is in straits because his '''baler''' is broken down and he's got three fields of hay ready to bale.''
# A person who creates bales, either by [[operate|operating]] or [[feed|feeding]] such a machine, or by creating the bales by hand.
#:''Hank worked as a '''baler''' for Farmer Jones part time, to make ends meet.''